	<definition>
		<title>Inductor</title>
		<statement>
			<p>An <term>inductor</term> is a wire coil<fn>commonly referred to as a solenoid</fn> used as a circuit element. The voltage across an inductor is given by <me>V_{inductor} = -L \frac{dI}{dt}</me>. Here, <m>L</m> is the inductance and it is measured in Henries (H). Inductors can also store energy given by <m>U_L = \frac{1}{2} L I^2</m>.</p>
		</statement>
	</definition>
	
